      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ACE VENTURA (8) was out of the money two runs back then again missed the frame last start over 1006m at this track, beaten 5.5 lengths into ninth after being in contention on the corner. Well placed and there is no reason he cannot find winning ways. DREWMAZING (1) finds it hard to win with four victories from 48 starts. Was again denied last start when he found a couple better over 1006m at this track. Best figures measure up nicely. Makes plenty of appeal. DONEGAL MOONSHINE (5) is back at the races for the first time since February 12. Worth noting he filled a minor placing when returning from a spell last prep over 1006m at Delta Downs. Looks a strong top-three prospect. DR NIKO (10) turned in a much better effort last time out to score by 2.25 lengths over 1207m at Fairgrounds (Dirt). Nicely placed to keep the ball rolling.",
